    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Up for sale is a driver-focused 2008 BMW M3 (E92) featuring the high-revving S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This power plant utilizes individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing to produce 414 hp at a staggering 8,300 RPM. Power is managed through a traditional 6-speed manual gearbox and a GKN-sourced variable M differential lock for optimal corner-exit traction. The chassis is equipped with Electronic Damping Control (EDC) and remains structurally rigid. This example is mechanically sorted, with preventative rod bearing replacement and throttle actuator service recently completed to ensure long-term reliability. While the exterior shows minor stone chips on the front fascia and the Novillo leather bolsters show slight patina, the kinematic performance remains sharp. It is a mechanically sound specimen that rewards a skilled hand behind the wheel.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
